		"title": "Continuous Delivery Workshop, part 1 of 3: Deployment Pipelines",
		"summary": "The first part of the workshop describes the technical differences between related topics such as *continuous integration*, *continuous deployment*, and *continuous delivery*, and describes the new technical artifact that Continuous Delivery introduces, the deployment pipeline. I discuss the various stages, how triggering works, and how to pragmatically determine what \"production ready\" means.\r\n",
