		"title": "Functional JavaScript",
		"summary": "JavaScript has a mixed heritage: OO and Functional. To date, us developers have focused on the OO side of JavaScript and not much mind-share has been given to the other, more powerful side. In this session we'll explore how to use the power of functional Javascript.",
		"detail": "JavaScript has elements of two distinct programming languages: Self and Scheme. These two languages are very different - and some of JavaScript's weirdness is due to this mixing of very different language designs. The conceptual models are also very different between Self and Scheme - one is a prototypical object based language, while the other is a functional language. In this session, we'll discuss the elements of how the Scheme functional programming language manifest in JavaScript. We're going to explore how you can write JavaScript in a more elegant and powerful way by applying functional concepts.",
