		"title": "You're an Architect...Now What?",
		"summary": "Many software developers point their career towards ascending to the gilded rank of Architect...but what does it mean to actually be one? While many of us labor under false pretense of abject technical decision making, the reality is often very different. You'll code less, spending more time on activities that lack an objective green/red bar. But you'll also an opportunity to impact far more than one project.\r\n\r\nIn this talk, I'll speak to my own journey. We'll touch on influencing coworkers, the importance of communication and the importance of cup of coffee.",
