		"title": "Reasoning: Working with What is Unsaid",
		"summary": "\"Computers are useless. They can only give you answers.\" --Picasso",
		"detail": "If everything is explicitly described in uniform, robust and comprehensive data models, it is easy to imagine how to ask questions of the data. The social, technical and financial costs of getting the information into that state, however, will keep that from ever being a reality. So, how can we integrate and reason over choppy and sloppy data from multiple sources in a variety of formats? We will see how the RDFS and Web Ontology Language (OWL) W3C standards help us connect and reason over content that leaves things unsaid without writing a bunch of custom code.\r\n\r\nThis is not artificial intelligence, but it is influenced by work done in that field. ",
		"prerequisite": "Data Integration, Linked Data",
